						<summary>

						<p>Slab standing in the temple of Vishṇumūrti.</p>						

						<p>Ballamahādēvī, 1279 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record refers to the fixation of tax payable from the village Beḷḷarpaḷḷi, by the queen in the presence of the members of her royal court. The record appears to be incomplete.</p>						

						<p>It is dated cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Pramādi, Jyēshṭha ba. 11, Mithuna 11, Wednesday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1279, A.D., June 6.</hi> The weekday was Tuesday.</p>						

						</summary>
